<org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmi:id="-SPwsOCDUxUNKS_7jBefo2g" name="uam_get_level_right,_7d1BgNEOEdyC2cfK_t2EKQ" guid="-SPwsOCDUxUNKS_7jBefo2g" authors="DW Enstrom" changeDate="2015-10-14T14:15:43.723-0400" version="2.0.0">
  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Consistent_Abstraction_Level&quot; name=&quot;XE_Best_Practices__Consistent_Abstraction_Level&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;table bordercolor=&quot;#ffffff&quot; width=&quot;100%&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;23%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;h3 dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
                    Introduction&#xD;
                &lt;/h3>&#xD;
                &lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot; align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
                    The architecture models are defined&amp;#160;by three perspectives or levels (i.e. Business, Logical,&#xD;
                    Technical) and with more or less detail as required. It is important to get both the level and level of&#xD;
                    detail very&amp;#160;clear at the start of an architecture effort: the&amp;#160;&lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
                    href=&quot;./../../../UAM/guidances/termdefinitions/uam_perspective_B4DE2D26.html&quot;&#xD;
                    guid=&quot;_6zOHAMJJEeKSedlRPHdUIQ&quot;>Architecture Perspective&lt;/a> and the level of detail needed&amp;#160;given&#xD;
                    the context and objective of the architecture.&amp;#160;&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;4%&quot;>&#xD;
                &amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td width=&quot;73%&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;table style=&quot;HEIGHT: 226px; WIDTH: 608px&quot; bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellpadding=&quot;5&quot; width=&quot;608&quot; border=&quot;3&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;16%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Benefits&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td width=&quot;84%&quot;>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Consistent Models&amp;#160;&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Reduced rehash, rework, and misunderstandings&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Longer lasting architecture models&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Pattern&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Agree the architectural view(s) required&amp;#160;&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Agree the level of detail required&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Agree the layers&amp;#160;used to manage complexity&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Consistent use of each view&amp;#160;&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Consistent level of detail in each view&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                        &lt;tr>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;strong>Anti-Patterns&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                            &lt;td>&#xD;
                                &lt;ul>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Artefacts in models are at multiple&amp;#160;levels&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Different views are at different levels of detail&amp;#160;&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                    &lt;li>&#xD;
                                        Nothing is agreed or&amp;#160;written down&amp;#160;&amp;#160;&#xD;
                                    &lt;/li>&#xD;
                                &lt;/ul>&#xD;
                            &lt;/td>&#xD;
                        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
                    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
                &lt;/table>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
        &lt;/tr>&#xD;
    &lt;/tbody>&#xD;
&lt;/table>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Discussion&amp;#160;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Communications is very important in defining architectures, which is greatly aided if the models created and the view&#xD;
    presented are consistent. Consistent in terms of the level of detail included (detail within layers and numbers of&#xD;
    layers) and consistent in terms of separation of information into the different views. This relates very much to&#xD;
    &quot;elevate the level of abstraction&quot;; that is, the level of abstraction chosen and used to define a model needs to be&#xD;
    consistently applied.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:PracticeDescription>
